    "Detailed information about the participants is provided in Table 1.",
    "Şencan (2005) and Tabachnick et al. (2019) suggest that, as a general rule, the sample size for scale development studies should be at least five times the number of items included.",
    "Thus, for a scale with 18 items, a minimum of 90 participants is recommended.",
    "However, this study exceeded this recommendation, reaching a sample size of 1006 participants.",
    "In sampling, the selected students were not chosen based on any criteria but instead randomly selected."
